title: Canada's oddest big roadside attractions | Canada | Travel | Toronto Sun
text: From the big nickel in Sudbury, Ont., to a giant Vincent van Gogh painting in Altona, Man., to the giant lobster in Shediac, N.B., Canada's highways are lined with some incredibly large, incredibly odd attractions. Check out our gallery of Canada's oddest, most amazing, biggest roadside attractions.
